lead_paragraph: Dave Warner smashed a sixth one-day international century of the year to drive Australia to a convincing 116-run victory over New Zealand as the hosts wrapped up the series with a match to spare in Canberra on Tuesday.

headline.print_headline: Six-Ton Warner Sees Australia Past New Zealand to Clinch Series
